ions.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(239,68,68,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(239,68,68,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#f87171; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eTrump \u0026amp; The Iran Situation\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Bond-Vigilante Handcuff:\u003c/strong\u003e With yields testing operational highs, the narrative frames the administration as financially pressured to cool the Iran conflict.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe 60-Day Extension:\u003c/strong\u003e Discussions of a formal 60-day extension ladder are described as deflating the immediate geopolitical risk premium.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEnergy Pipeline Deflation:\u003c/strong\u003e Reflecting these progressions, Brent crude is cited near $92/bbl, stripping speculative heat out of the inflation transmission pipeline.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#fbbf24; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eFed Chair Kevin Warsh Remarks\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAI Productivity Framework:\u003c/strong\u003e Warsh is described as basing his rate framework on the thesis that AI productivity gains act as an aggressive deflationary force, leaning into the expansionary backdrop.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Rate-Cut Repricing:\u003c/strong\u003e The draft model argues rates markets will reprice toward one cut before year-end, citing the pattern that incoming Chairs cut within their first 12 months. Treat as narrative, not confirmed policy guidance.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128200; Trading Strategy Note (ES Futures)\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Breakout Matrix:\u003c/strong\u003e The framework reads the late-April swing-high takeout and the May 1st clearance of the April 30th high as a daily candle taking a monthly high \u0026#8212; the technical signature of a mega-trend breakout.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTarget Levels:\u003c/strong\u003e Structural projections are revised upward, with a Wall Street high call of 8,447\u0026#8211;8,477 on S\u0026amp;P 500 futures into the year-end cycle.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOrder-Flow Execution:\u003c/strong\u003e During the 22:00 GMT+8 ISM Manufacturing window, watch the 1.5k volume chart in MotiveWave for stop-hunts. With the trend on an absolute daily bull layout, treat sharp flushes into the Value Area Low as structural buying rather than fading all-time-high expansions.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(148,163,184,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Williams Rule:\u003c/strong\u003e While the bullet train is highly active, keep position sizing disciplined relative to the broader natural cycle, which marks June 16th for the formation of the ultimate sustainable base.\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e"
